class Resnet(nn.Module):
        def __init__(self,in_channel,out_classes):
            super().__init__()
            self.layer1=conv_block(in_channel,64)
            self.layer2=conv_block(64,128,pool=True)
            self.res1  =nn.Sequential(conv_block(128,128),conv_block(128,128))
            self.layer3=conv_block(128,256,pool=True)
            self.layer4=conv_block(256,512,pool=True)
            self.res2  =nn.Sequential(conv_block(512,512),conv_block(512,512))
            self.layer5=nn.Sequential(nn.MaxPool2d(4),
                                  nn.Flatten(),
                                  nn.Linear(512,out_classes))
        
        def forward(self,x):
            out=self.layer1(x)
            out=self.layer2(out)
            out=self.res1(out)+out
            out=self.layer3(out)
            out=self.layer4(out)
            out=self.res2(out)+out
            out=self.layer5(out)
            return(out)
        
    
model=Resnet(3,7)
model

loss_fn=F.cross_entropy
torch.cuda.empty_cache()
train_loss=[]
val_loss=[]
train_acc=[]
val_acc=[]
    
def fit(epochs,lr,model,opt_func=torch.optim.SGD):

    for epoch in range(epochs):
        optimizer=opt_func(model.parameters(),lr=1e-3)
        model.train()
        score=0
        for batch in train_dl:
            x,y=batch
            if torch.cuda.is_available():
                x=x.cuda()
                y=y.cuda()
                
            
            #STEP-1: Forward
            out=model(x)
        
            #STEP-2:Loss
            loss=loss_fn(out,y)
        
            #Step-3:Cleaning the prev calculated gradients
            model.zero_grad()
        
            #Step-4:Accumalate partial derivatives of Loss wrt to params
            loss.backward()
        
            #Step-5: Takes 5 steps to update
            optimizer.step()
            _,pred=torch.max(out,axis=1)
            score+=(pred==y).sum()
        acc=score/len(train_ds)
        
        # Validation Set
        score_val=0
        for batch in valid_dl:
            images,labels=batch
            if torch.cuda.is_available():
                images=images.cuda()
                labels=labels.cuda()
            out=model(images)
            val_loss=loss_fn(out,labels)
            _,pred_val=torch.max(out,axis=1)
            score_val+=(pred_val==labels).sum()

        val_acc=score_val/len(valid_ds)
        
        train_loss.append(loss)
        #val_loss.append(val_loss)
        train_acc.append(acc)
        #val_acc.append(val_acc)
        print("{}/{} Epochs  | Train Loss={:.4f}  |Train_Accuracy={:.4f} |Val_loss={:.4f}  |Val_Accuracy={:.4f}".format(epoch+1,epochs,loss,acc,val_loss,val_acc)  )
